WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.910
I don't want them to see my face!

3
00:01:46.910 --> 00:01:50.140
If they do, they'll kill me!

4
00:01:50.140 --> 00:01:51.560
Shut up!

5
00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:55.490
They already know it's you.

6
00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:58.330
Those guys are obviously
wreaking havoc using your ability!

7
00:02:00.300 --> 00:02:05.040
Okay! This mirror is the linchpin
for the allied forces to escape.

8
00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:08.910
Once I complete this task,
I'll get my heart back.

9
00:02:08.910 --> 00:02:12.920
And once I have it,
I'll teach all of them a lesson!

10
00:02:16.180 --> 00:02:19.920
<b>Hey, Mother</b>

11
00:02:25.230 --> 00:02:27.330
How's everything going inside?

12
00:02:28.610 --> 00:02:32.150
I'm not hearing any shrieks yet...
What's Big Mom doing?

13
00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:39.410
Just as we planned...

14
00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:44.110
The cake is busted...
and the flock of Straw Hats are on the loose...

15
00:02:44.750 --> 00:02:49.520
The portrait of Mother Carmel
is broken, too...

16
00:02:49.950 --> 00:02:53.220
So why isn't Big Mom shrieking?!

17
00:02:56.820 --> 00:02:58.720
What's going on?!

18
00:03:04.300 --> 00:03:07.070
Luffy-san, listen to me!

19
00:03:07.070 --> 00:03:10.740
Big Mom has experienced too many shocks
in quick succession,

20
00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:13.910
so she doesn't know
how to focus her anger.

21
00:03:14.340 --> 00:03:17.940
Okay! I'll do it if you think it's best!

22
00:03:20.180 --> 00:03:21.950
Leave it to me!

23
00:03:24.220 --> 00:03:28.350
Stop Straw Hat!
Don't let him get close to Mama!

24
00:03:38.520 --> 00:03:41.230
Why are you getting in my way?!

25
00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:48.140
Bege!

26
00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:54.680
Bege, you bastard...

27
00:03:58.580 --> 00:04:00.990
Go to hell, Katakuri!

28
00:04:03.360 --> 00:04:06.660
What are you doing, Gang Bege?!

29
00:04:09.230 --> 00:04:12.000
I knew you'd betray us, Bege...

30
00:04:16.140 --> 00:04:18.340
Brother Peros!

31
00:04:17.070 --> 00:04:18.340
Hm?

32
00:04:18.340 --> 00:04:20.970
Hurry up and shoot them!

33
00:04:20.970 --> 00:04:22.310
Yeah, I know.

34
00:04:24.810 --> 00:04:28.780
Goodness...
The future-seeing man sure is busy...

35
00:04:29.250 --> 00:04:34.790
But in this one situation,
I, too, can see the future.

36
00:04:37.220 --> 00:04:42.730
Trapped in my candy,
you'll all die with pathetic looks on your faces.

37
00:04:44.860 --> 00:04:46.630
There can be no other outcome!

38
00:04:50.270 --> 00:04:53.740
If only we had our raid suits...

39
00:04:53.740 --> 00:04:56.580
you would not have gotten away with this!

40
00:04:56.580 --> 00:04:57.880
Raid?

41
00:04:58.610 --> 00:05:02.920
What's that? Is it some kind of weapon?
Lick.

42
00:05:04.780 --> 00:05:09.620
Whoa-whoa, why would you want to bring
such a thing to your son's wedding?

43
00:05:12.320 --> 00:05:14.530
Get out of there, Reiju!

44
00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:25.840
It's you again!

45
00:05:29.140 --> 00:05:31.310
Don't get in my way!

46
00:05:37.680 --> 00:05:39.350
Sanji...

47
00:05:39.350 --> 00:05:43.190
What is he doing?
He's causing trouble...

48
00:05:55.870 --> 00:05:56.740
Sanji...

49
00:05:58.470 --> 00:06:01.310
I underestimated your kindness.

50
00:06:01.310 --> 00:06:06.010
Even after everything we've done to you,
you still won't abandon us.

51
00:06:08.310 --> 00:06:10.680
I've always hated being a Vinsmoke

52
00:06:11.380 --> 00:06:13.320
and have always been ashamed of it.

53
00:06:14.390 --> 00:06:14.890
But...

54
00:06:15.950 --> 00:06:18.060
when I saw you all grown up...

55
00:06:20.990 --> 00:06:24.230
I felt relieved!

56
00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:33.610
Because I realized that we still had a conscience in our bloodline...

57
00:06:35.310 --> 00:06:38.310
Thank you... Sanji!

58
00:06:46.350 --> 00:06:49.120
Oh, no! Sanji's family is...

59
00:07:09.110 --> 00:07:09.980
You bastard!

60
00:07:11.210 --> 00:07:12.180
Pedro!

61
00:07:12.180 --> 00:07:14.580
Don't touch it, Luffy! Go!

62
00:07:14.580 --> 00:07:15.150
Thanks!

63
00:07:16.350 --> 00:07:19.350
Five Thousand Tile...

64
00:07:19.350 --> 00:07:21.350
Fist!

65
00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:32.030
Bege!

66
00:07:33.870 --> 00:07:36.100
Drop dead, Katakuri!

67
00:07:44.540 --> 00:07:45.740
Oh no, you don't!

68
00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:03.300
Mama...

69
00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:12.300
Mama... No!

70
00:08:22.010 --> 00:08:22.780
M...

71
00:08:23.480 --> 00:08:25.280
Mother...

72
00:08:25.950 --> 00:08:26.490
M...

73
00:08:34.830 --> 00:08:36.290
Mother!

74
00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:41.830
Mama!

75
00:08:52.710 --> 00:08:54.180
All right!

76
00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:41.790
Now, take care of the rest by yourselves.

77
00:10:41.790 --> 00:10:43.520
Well, I guess they can't hear me.

78
00:11:05.310 --> 00:11:06.910
Mama got injured?!

79
00:11:09.310 --> 00:11:11.180
She's weakened!

80
00:11:20.290 --> 00:11:23.260
Hey! Somebody stop Bege and his men!

81
00:11:28.870 --> 00:11:29.770
Bege!

82
00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:33.140
How dare you betray us!

83
00:11:33.140 --> 00:11:35.840
Farewell, Big Mom!

84
00:11:41.610 --> 00:11:42.580
Mother...

85
00:11:43.520 --> 00:11:46.590
Hey... Listen, Mother.

86
00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:52.290
Nobody will listen to me.

87
00:11:53.120 --> 00:11:57.600
Hey, Mother... Where did you go?

88
00:11:59.330 --> 00:12:01.300
Big Mom's tears...

89
00:12:02.570 --> 00:12:08.670
This story goes back 63 years,
to Elbaf in the New World.

90
00:12:09.540 --> 00:12:15.550
The island home of the warriors of Elbaf,
the most famous of all the giants.

91
00:12:29.630 --> 00:12:31.000
Now, come on.

92
00:12:34.470 --> 00:12:38.470
<b>Charlotte Linlin
(Human, Five Years Old)</b>

93
00:12:35.770 --> 00:12:38.470
What is this place?

94
00:12:38.470 --> 00:12:43.140
I'll tell you later.
Hurry and come down from there, Linlin.

95
00:12:43.140 --> 00:12:44.540
Uh-huh!

96
00:12:45.180 --> 00:12:46.310
Here I come!

97
00:12:50.420 --> 00:12:51.750
Hey, hey.

98
00:12:52.720 --> 00:12:57.420
Where are we?
Are you going somewhere?

99
00:12:57.420 --> 00:13:00.160
Papa has a job to do nearby.

100
00:13:00.160 --> 00:13:03.030
Linlin, will you be a good girl and wait for us here?

101
00:13:03.030 --> 00:13:05.730
What?! I wanna come with you...

102
00:13:05.730 --> 00:13:09.600
If you're a good girl, you can eat
all the candy in your backpack that you want!

103
00:13:09.600 --> 00:13:11.000
That's right!

104
00:13:11.440 --> 00:13:12.940
What?!

105
00:13:12.940 --> 00:13:15.340
All of it?!
Then, I'll wait, I'll wait!

106
00:13:15.770 --> 00:13:18.640
I'll wait for you!

107
00:13:21.950 --> 00:13:23.280
See you later!

108
00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:25.580
Hurry back!

109
00:13:27.920 --> 00:13:29.190
Linlin...

110
00:13:29.190 --> 00:13:30.090
Don't cry yet.

111
00:13:31.290 --> 00:13:35.060
After all the damage she caused,
we're lucky she's only being exiled.

112
00:13:35.660 --> 00:13:38.200
She's just... too much for us to handle.

113
00:13:39.230 --> 00:13:43.340
They say the Holy Mother lives here.
She'll save Linlin.

114
00:13:43.940 --> 00:13:47.170
Let's set off! We're in a dangerous area!

115
00:13:56.180 --> 00:13:58.350
See you!

116
00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:04.190
Wow! Those are some big fish.

117
00:14:08.530 --> 00:14:10.760
GROWL...

118
00:14:12.300 --> 00:14:16.200
This is weird.
They're taking too long.

119
00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:18.240
I'm getting hungry...

120
00:14:19.340 --> 00:14:22.770
Mama, Papa, where did you go?

121
00:14:23.210 --> 00:14:25.940
Why aren't you back yet?!

122
00:14:31.320 --> 00:14:32.850
As for Elbaf,

123
00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:39.620
a century ago, it was home to giant warriors
that were feared by the entire world.

124
00:14:39.620 --> 00:14:41.890
They were the Giant Warrior Pirates!

125
00:14:43.660 --> 00:14:49.070
They terrorized the entire world
and burned down countless cities.

126
00:14:50.400 --> 00:14:51.240
However,

127
00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:57.740
when the Giant Warrior Pirates'
two captains suddenly vanished...

128
00:14:57.740 --> 00:14:59.710
they passed into legend.

129
00:14:59.710 --> 00:15:02.480
Shortly afterward, several of the remaining members,

130
00:15:02.480 --> 00:15:04.250
careless after the loss of their leaders...

131
00:15:04.250 --> 00:15:08.090
wound up being captured by the Navy and sentenced to death.

132
00:15:08.090 --> 00:15:10.220
Kill them!

133
00:15:19.200 --> 00:15:20.570
Please wait!

134
00:15:21.970 --> 00:15:23.560
Stop the execution!

135
00:15:23.570 --> 00:15:26.270
Heaven seeks a peaceful understanding!

136
00:15:28.210 --> 00:15:31.510
Until the appearance of a wandering holy woman!

137
00:15:31.510 --> 00:15:34.380
Her name was Sister Carmel.

138
00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:35.150
<b>Sister Carmel</b>

139
00:15:35.150 --> 00:15:38.350
Heaven seeks what?!
What nonsense are you talking about?!

140
00:15:38.350 --> 00:15:41.290
Do you know how much terror
they've caused–

141
00:15:41.290 --> 00:15:44.120
An even greater reason for penance!
Why can't you see that?

142
00:15:54.930 --> 00:15:56.840
If you kill those men,

143
00:15:56.840 --> 00:16:02.570
the warriors of Elbaf will form an army
to get their revenge against humanity!

144
00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:05.410
Forgive their crimes!

145
00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:16.120
I will guide them!

146
00:16:21.630 --> 00:16:23.960
To a world where all races join hands

147
00:16:26.130 --> 00:16:27.970
and laugh together!

148
00:16:30.200 --> 00:16:35.170
In time, she became "Mother" Carmel,
and founded an orphanage

149
00:16:35.170 --> 00:16:38.080
called the House of Lambs,
where she took in children

150
00:16:38.080 --> 00:16:41.410
without anywhere else to go,
regardless of their status or race.

151
00:16:43.050 --> 00:16:45.580
On Elbaf, the homeland of the giants,

152
00:16:46.720 --> 00:16:50.460
she served as a diplomatic bridge to unite humanity and giants.

153
00:16:53.560 --> 00:16:56.190
And then, 37 years later...

154
00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:59.800
It'll be okay, Linlin.

155
00:16:57.020 --> 00:17:02.830
<b>Mother Carmel (80 Years Old)
And the Children of the House of Lambs</b>

156
00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:03.540
We can all live together in happiness until your parents come back!

157
00:17:03.540 --> 00:17:07.210
They won't come back!
You've been abandoned!

158
00:17:07.210 --> 00:17:10.610
All of the children here are quite interesting.

159
00:17:10.610 --> 00:17:12.440
Interesting enough for our parents to give us up!

160
00:17:14.450 --> 00:17:16.450
You'll be friends in no time.

161
00:17:16.450 --> 00:17:19.150
Uh-huh! Thank you!

162
00:17:19.150 --> 00:17:21.250
I'm starving!

163
00:17:21.250 --> 00:17:23.720
You're huge! Are you a giant?

164
00:17:23.720 --> 00:17:26.020
In that case, let's eat!

165
00:17:26.020 --> 00:17:29.960
There was a prince chased out
of his country after a coup...

166
00:17:30.320 --> 00:17:33.400
and impoverished children
who nearly fell into slavery...

167
00:17:34.030 --> 00:17:37.170
Problem children whose parents
couldn't handle them...

168
00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:41.970
All of them lived in a giant village
where their pasts couldn't haunt them.

169
00:17:43.840 --> 00:17:45.040
Hey, Mother!

170
00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:47.750
Is she new?

171
00:17:47.080 --> 00:17:47.760
Huh?

172
00:17:50.110 --> 00:17:55.580
But most importantly of all, for Linlin,
who was always bigger than everyone else,

173
00:17:55.590 --> 00:17:57.760
Elbaf was the first place

174
00:17:57.760 --> 00:18:02.760
where the people, homes, and sights were her size.

175
00:18:02.760 --> 00:18:04.700
It was a comforting place for her.

176
00:18:05.560 --> 00:18:09.370
This is great!

177
00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:13.650
<b>The Next Day...</b>

178
00:18:14.070 --> 00:18:18.110
Why did it happen? Why did it happen?

179
00:18:20.140 --> 00:18:22.780
Oh, no. What's the matter, Linlin?

180
00:18:23.780 --> 00:18:26.250
Mother, listen...

181
00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:31.990
A bear and a wolf were
fighting in the forest.

182
00:18:31.990 --> 00:18:36.090
I wanted them to be friends
because fighting is bad,

183
00:18:36.090 --> 00:18:39.330
so I put them in the same cage yesterday.

184
00:18:39.330 --> 00:18:44.000
But then Bear-san ate Wolf-san !

185
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:46.840
That's why I hit Bear-san.

186
00:18:47.610 --> 00:18:51.110
Bear-san looks sorry now.
How many times did you hit him?

187
00:18:51.940 --> 00:18:53.380
Just once...

188
00:18:55.180 --> 00:18:58.050
Instant... death?!

189
00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:07.360
Oh, I understand!

190
00:19:07.360 --> 00:19:10.630
You just wanted them to be friends!

191
00:19:11.230 --> 00:19:13.830
Linlin, you're such a sweet girl!

192
00:19:15.200 --> 00:19:16.570
Uh-huh!

193
00:19:16.570 --> 00:19:20.140
Then, let's go play with everyone else!

194
00:19:20.140 --> 00:19:21.110
Uh-huh!

195
00:19:23.640 --> 00:19:28.950
To Linlin, Carmel was the first person ever
to really understand her.

196
00:19:29.980 --> 00:19:34.190
I saw it! Linlin killed a
bear with a single hit!

197
00:19:34.190 --> 00:19:35.820
She's dangerous!

198
00:19:36.220 --> 00:19:39.320
Did you hear that she injured Eiri-kun, the giant?

199
00:19:39.920 --> 00:19:42.830
She was only smacking him to hit a mosquito!

200
00:19:43.490 --> 00:19:45.460
She broke lots of his bones!

201
00:19:47.130 --> 00:19:49.330
Ouch! Ouch!

202
00:19:49.330 --> 00:19:51.970
What are you doing, Linlin?

203
00:19:51.970 --> 00:19:52.970
What?

204
00:19:53.770 --> 00:19:55.710
Mother! Help!

205
00:19:55.710 --> 00:20:00.650
Well, he has an extra joint,
so I was gonna rip it off for him.

206
00:20:00.650 --> 00:20:04.650
No, he's a longarm!
It's normal for them!

207
00:20:04.650 --> 00:20:07.350
Oh... I see...

208
00:20:09.020 --> 00:20:10.420
Ouch!

209
00:20:10.420 --> 00:20:12.990
Linlin, what are you doing?!

210
00:20:12.990 --> 00:20:16.230
He has fins,
so I was gonna rip them off for him.

211
00:20:16.230 --> 00:20:20.730
Don't do that.
Fishmen have the physical traits of fish.

212
00:20:20.730 --> 00:20:23.130
Oh... I see...

213
00:20:24.470 --> 00:20:25.640
I was terrified!

214
00:20:33.140 --> 00:20:35.380
Everyone, forgive her!

215
00:20:35.380 --> 00:20:38.080
Linlin is a kind girl!

216
00:20:42.690 --> 00:20:45.420
Carmel forgave everything.

217
00:20:48.330 --> 00:20:49.230
Wait, wait!

218
00:20:49.230 --> 00:20:50.330
No!

219
00:20:51.860 --> 00:20:53.900
Linlin's gonna kill us!

220
00:20:53.900 --> 00:20:57.140
Wait, wait! Wait, wait!

221
00:20:57.140 --> 00:21:01.140
Ten months later in Elbaf, the Land of War,
in the New World,

222
00:20:57.170 --> 00:20:59.400
<b>Kashi</b>

223
00:21:01.140 --> 00:21:05.580
the mighty warriors
welcomed Linlin with open arms.

224
00:21:01.870 --> 00:21:04.380
<b>Oimo</b>

225
00:21:06.780 --> 00:21:08.680
Wait, wait!

226
00:21:09.180 --> 00:21:11.420
It's almost been 40 years...

227
00:21:13.220 --> 00:21:15.550
Have you ever seen a duel last this long?

228
00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:21.430
Oimo agrees!
Let's go get them in 10 years!

229
00:21:25.130 --> 00:21:28.730
Hey, Linlin!
Did you guys finish preparing?

230
00:21:30.940 --> 00:21:33.040
Kashi, preparing for what?

231
00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:37.070
Oh, Linlin-chan, I guess
it's your first time.

232
00:21:37.580 --> 00:21:41.880
Before the Winter Solstice Festival, Elbaf fasts for 12 days!

233
00:21:42.910 --> 00:21:44.350
A fast?

234
00:21:44.350 --> 00:21:48.320
We won't be eating anything.
We're only allowed to drink water.

235
00:21:48.890 --> 00:21:51.120
That's 12 days starting tomorrow!

236
00:21:51.120 --> 00:21:52.020
What?!

237
00:21:53.220 --> 00:21:55.490
I'm gonna be hungry!

238
00:21:55.490 --> 00:21:58.700
But if you can endure it,
we'll have a festival!

239
00:22:03.070 --> 00:22:05.570
Your true opponent is yourself, Hajrudin!

240
00:22:07.840 --> 00:22:09.510
Stand up, Hajrudin!

241
00:22:16.350 --> 00:22:21.060
<b>Hajrudin</b>

242
00:22:16.750 --> 00:22:20.120
This giant boy, Hajrudin...

243
00:22:20.120 --> 00:22:25.390
will eventually meet Luffy on Dressrosa,
and be impressed by his determination.

244
00:22:26.260 --> 00:22:27.730
Along with Bartolomeo and the others,

245
00:22:27.730 --> 00:22:30.190
he exchanged cups of sake as
parent and son with Luffy.

246
00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:34.700
He is now a member of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet.

247
00:22:36.700 --> 00:22:38.240
The tough boy!

248
00:22:39.100 --> 00:22:44.210
Either Chief Dorry or Chief Brogy will return,

249
00:22:44.210 --> 00:22:47.380
and the Giant Warrior Pirates
will be reformed!

250
00:22:47.380 --> 00:22:49.380
You're a warrior!

251
00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:51.880
You've got to discipline yourself, Hajrudin!

252
00:22:51.280 --> 00:22:51.880
Yeah!

253
00:22:53.650 --> 00:22:56.720
I like that spirit, Raideen!

254
00:22:56.720 --> 00:22:57.520
Uh-huh!

255
00:23:06.300 --> 00:23:13.820
<b>"Mountain Beard" Jarl
(345 Years Old)</b>
<b>"Waterfall Beard" Jorl
(344 Years Old)</b>

256
00:23:06.930 --> 00:23:09.500
Chief Waterfall Beard and Chief Mountain Beard!

257
00:23:09.500 --> 00:23:12.270
Carmel's ideas about trade over plunder

258
00:23:12.270 --> 00:23:14.010
are all well and good.

259
00:23:14.010 --> 00:23:17.910
But we must not forget the fact that we are warriors!

260
00:23:17.910 --> 00:23:19.080
Yes!

261
00:23:19.080 --> 00:23:22.250
The chiefs Jarl and Jorl are so cool!

262
00:23:22.250 --> 00:23:26.180
<b>Former Co-Captains of the
Giant Warrior Pirates
(Two of the World's Oldest Warriors)
Heroes of the Giants</b>

263
00:23:22.750 --> 00:23:26.180
The most respected warriors of giantkind!

264
00:23:26.180 --> 00:23:29.090
I wanna be like them some day!

265
00:23:30.890 --> 00:23:33.120
What are you two doing here today?

266
00:23:33.890 --> 00:23:38.800
We're here to eat semlor in the village. We've come
to call on the children from the House of Lambs.
"(sing.)semla/(pl.)semlor" - traditional Swedish sweet roll

267
00:23:38.800 --> 00:23:41.530
It's good to see you, Linlin.

268
00:23:41.530 --> 00:23:43.170
What're Semlor ?

269
00:23:43.170 --> 00:23:45.340
They're sweet, delicious treats!

270
00:23:45.340 --> 00:23:46.770
What?! Sweets?

271
00:23:46.770 --> 00:23:50.470
Eating semlor before the fast
will give us lots of nutrients!

272
00:23:50.470 --> 00:23:55.180
Are we gonna eat them now? The sweets?!

273
00:23:55.180 --> 00:24:00.320
Sweet cream dolloped
in sweet bread with marzipan,

274
00:24:00.320 --> 00:24:02.490
topped with a dusting of sugar!

275
00:24:02.490 --> 00:24:04.920
It's the fun before the fast!

276
00:24:04.920 --> 00:24:07.120
Sounds delicious!

277
00:24:10.460 --> 00:24:12.500
All right, everyone!

278
00:24:12.500 --> 00:24:17.540
We celebrate the recent birth
of Prince Loki at the castle. And...

279
00:24:17.540 --> 00:24:21.410
the births of Road and Goldberg in the village!

280
00:24:21.410 --> 00:24:25.310
We thank the sun for their growth!

281
00:24:25.310 --> 00:24:26.910
Thank the sun!

282
00:24:26.910 --> 00:24:29.650
Thank you for the food!

283
00:24:29.650 --> 00:24:31.550
Yeah! Semlor !

284
00:24:31.550 --> 00:24:33.820
There's plenty for everyone!

285
00:24:39.920 --> 00:24:41.830
So sweet!

286
00:24:42.330 --> 00:24:44.000
It's delicious!

287
00:24:44.400 --> 00:24:46.660
I'm happy!

288
00:24:51.470 --> 00:24:54.570
Delicious! Delicious! Sweet! Sweet!
Delicious! Delicious!

289
00:24:54.570 --> 00:24:55.670
Delicious! Delicious!

290
00:25:03.410 --> 00:25:06.020
Delicious! Delicious! Delic–

291
00:25:03.780 --> 00:25:06.020
Whoa, wait! Hey, Linlin!

292
00:25:06.020 --> 00:25:09.950
Don't eat so fast!
There won't be enough to go around!

293
00:25:09.950 --> 00:25:12.820
Don't forget to thank the sun!

294
00:25:13.560 --> 00:25:16.560
Semlor !

295
00:25:19.160 --> 00:25:25.170
It's delicious! It's so delicious! Semlor !

296
00:25:28.270 --> 00:25:32.280
<b>Day 3 of the Fast</b>

297
00:25:29.240 --> 00:25:32.680
Mother... I'm starving to death...

298
00:25:32.680 --> 00:25:36.850
The Winter Solstice Festival celebrates
the death and rebirth of the sun.

299
00:25:36.850 --> 00:25:42.920
After the harsh winter,
the sun will shine down on us again.

300
00:25:43.050 --> 00:25:45.290
<b>Day 4 of the Fast</b>

301
00:25:45.290 --> 00:25:50.230
The more we suffer,
the more we will appreciate the sun.

302
00:25:50.230 --> 00:25:52.730
So... let's keep going!

303
00:25:56.370 --> 00:26:01.140
If Mother says so, I'll... keep trying...

304
00:26:03.370 --> 00:26:05.880
<b>Day 5 of the Fast</b>

305
00:26:07.110 --> 00:26:08.480
I'm getting skinnier...

306
00:26:08.480 --> 00:26:10.050
You haven't changed.

307
00:26:10.050 --> 00:26:13.050
Oh yeah? That's strange...

308
00:26:13.050 --> 00:26:13.920
Linlin!

309
00:26:15.320 --> 00:26:17.920
You're doing great! Just a little more to go!

310
00:26:19.290 --> 00:26:19.890
Uh-huh!

311
00:26:20.460 --> 00:26:23.760
Linlin truly loved Mother.

312
00:26:24.130 --> 00:26:26.630
<b>Day 6 of the Fast</b>

313
00:26:27.700 --> 00:26:30.470
The semlor were so delicious...

314
00:26:32.670 --> 00:26:33.840
I...

315
00:26:35.310 --> 00:26:38.210
want to have more.

316
00:26:43.180 --> 00:26:45.680
<b>Day 7 of the Fast</b>

317
00:26:48.920 --> 00:26:50.190
Oh, no!

318
00:26:53.290 --> 00:26:54.790
Mother, help!

319
00:26:56.630 --> 00:26:58.030
What's the matter, Gerd?!

320
00:27:00.130 --> 00:27:01.670
Linlin-chan is...!

321
00:27:10.010 --> 00:27:10.770
This is...

322
00:27:12.010 --> 00:27:16.510
Semlor !

323
00:27:16.510 --> 00:27:17.680
How could you...?

324
00:27:18.280 --> 00:27:19.250
Linlin!

325
00:27:19.750 --> 00:27:22.950
Bring me semlor...

326
00:27:22.950 --> 00:27:26.520
Semlor !

327
00:27:28.960 --> 00:27:32.230
Linlin destroyed the village of Elbaf!

328
00:27:32.860 --> 00:27:34.400
It's a nightmare!

329
00:27:37.130 --> 00:27:42.340
You've made a grave mistake, Linlin!
You do not have the right to thank the sun!

330
00:27:42.340 --> 00:27:45.680
Even a child can only be forgiven for so much!

331
00:27:45.680 --> 00:27:46.980
Chief Jorl!

332
00:27:46.980 --> 00:27:49.910
Semlor... Semlor...

333
00:27:49.910 --> 00:27:52.420
Carmel... I'm sorry...

334
00:27:52.420 --> 00:27:55.520
She may look like a child...

335
00:27:55.520 --> 00:27:57.350
Don't do it, Chief Jorl!

336
00:27:57.350 --> 00:27:59.090
...but she's a demon!

337
00:28:08.570 --> 00:28:15.510
Semlor...
